      "writtenOn": "2016-01-11T16:49:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "On batch files, because it\u0027s a feature that cmd.exe implements for legacy reasons. Otherwise, each Win32 process has a single current directory, made of a drive/server designator, and a path on the corresponding volume. See [1]\n\nI think you\u0027re the one who gave me this link earlier.\n\nGiven that we\u0027re not implementing a cmd.exe replacement, I think it\u0027s ok not to deal with this edge case and just leave this as that.\n\nI\u0027m a bit surprised the result isn\u0027t C:\\\\home\\\\testdir\\\\D:home though. Not sure if this matters though.\n\n[1] https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20101011-00/?p\u003d12563",
